    "completionRequirements": "![](https://ck3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/06/Icon_piety_judaism_01.png/24px-Icon_piety_judaism_01.png) Jewish religion  \n\n![](https://ck3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/01/Kingdom.png/24px-Kingdom.png) Kingdom or Empire title  \n![Yes](https://ck3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/0f/Icon_check.png/24px-Icon_check.png) Has created a divergent culture\n\n![Yes](https://ck3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/0/0f/Icon_check.png/24px-Icon_check.png) Capital province is in east Africa",
    "notes": "Start as King of Abyssinia in any start date, gain ![](https://ck3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/f/fa/Icon_piety_christian_01.png/24px-Icon_piety_christian_01.png) Piety and convert to Haymanot. You can keep restarting to get the ![](https://ck3.paradoxwikis.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Trait_cynical.png/24px-Trait_cynical.png) Cynical trait to make this easier. The cost of creating a divergent culture increases with Realm size, so keeping the realm small will make this easier to achieve. If the Realm is large, you can grant titles and transfer vassals to one of your vassals who isn't in your De Jure territory and grant them independence to drastically reduce the Realm size."
